notesStmt.note: Defective at the beginning and at the end.
Margins as well as first and last few folios much damaged.
Additional comments in different handwriting are found throughout in the margins.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: A daily prayer book according to the German rite, with a commentary.

msItem.title: Special portions for Rosh ḥodesh etc.
Prayers for Rosh ha-Shanah and Yom Kipur
Ma῾ariv for the first day of Pesaḥ

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 2; ruled lines: 14 51; written lines: 12 49; Non-uniform layout, with varying number of lines a page. Visible pricking and hard-point ruling. Initial words written in larger characters. Some letters written in red ink (see folios 127v-135r). Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable. Most of the margins are occupied with the commentary. The left margin left for commentary by the scribe has also in some cases been cut away (e.g., folios 86, 97-98). Censor's erasures, e.g., folios 30v, 38r.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Ashkenazi square and semi-cursive script, partially punctuated, of the 13th to 14th century.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'Tephilloth, with Comm. of El'azar of Worms. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,556.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Samuel Schönblum of Vienna: purchased from him on 08 December 1866: inscribed (folio [190v]).
